messages.messageBody:
--- simionescu silviu <zabara_klan@...> wrote:

> what is the translation of Ieyasu Tokugawa baner. i
> am waiting for some answers . thanyou!

Can you be more specific as to which particular banner
you mean? If you had a link to a picture or something,
it would be extremely helpful.

If anyone wants help translating something from
Japanese, there are several of us (probably more than
that) that can help. But you've got to set yourself up
for success--by just throwing the question out there,
not only do I now have to translate said banner, I've
got to go looking for it, confirm it's the CORRECT
banner this person wants to know about, and then
translate it. It may be as simple as me going to
google, typing in "Ieyasu Banner" and getting a
picture. But if you really want your questions
answered, then you should do the legwork. This board
isn't here to compensate for your laziness/lack of
effort. There's no reason you can't go to Google, find
what you're looking for, and then provide us the link
to look at so we can help.

Thanks,

The Assistant Management.
